summary:
The Security Council, 
Recalling previous resolutions and statements on Somalia, 
Determining the situation in Somalia remains a threat to international peace and security, 
Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter, 
1. Reaffirms resolution 2662 (2022); 
2. Renews provisions on arms embargo, set out in paragraphs 15 and 17 of resolution 2182 (2014) and expanded to cover IED components by paragraph 5 of resolution 2607 (2021), until 1 December 2023; 
3. Renews the mandate of the Panel of Experts until 31 December 2023, and intends to review the mandate and take action on any extension and modification, including restrictions on the import of weapons and ammunition by Somalia, by 1 December 2023; 
4. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
